17:23.284 --> 17:26.152
and someday standing
a few feet from Jamie

17:26.204 --> 17:27.537
and taking his life.

17:29.407 --> 17:31.691
And that's impossible and horrible...
Mm.

17:31.742 --> 17:33.693
...And that's <i>exactly</i>
<i>what my father did.</i>

17:35.880 --> 17:38.031
And then I feel guilty...

17:38.082 --> 17:40.383
For keeping Jamie
from seeing his grandfather

17:40.468 --> 17:42.869
and for making it
to the NBA

17:42.920 --> 17:45.171
and knowing that I never could
have done it without my father.

17:47.258 --> 17:50.310
And for letting him live alone
and die alone

17:50.377 --> 17:52.095
because that's what
I have to do.

17:54.315 --> 17:58.852
Maybe you should just
go to that diner

17:58.903 --> 18:02.606
and tell Dan everything that
you're thinking and feeling --

18:02.690 --> 18:04.174
all of it.

18:04.242 --> 18:05.725
You think
he deserves that?

18:05.776 --> 18:07.360
No.

18:09.080 --> 18:10.797
But I think
you deserve it.

18:13.134 --> 18:16.202
♪ Aah, aah, aah, aah, aah ♪

18:25.223 --> 18:27.358
Hey, didn't you already
work out today?

18:27.442 --> 18:30.978
Yep.
I'm doing two-a-days.

18:31.029 --> 18:34.031
Oh. You're worried about
being around all those models.

18:34.115 --> 18:35.566
Mm, actually,
that's not it.

18:35.650 --> 18:37.651
I'm worried about
security at the airport.

18:37.702 --> 18:39.153
What?

18:39.204 --> 18:41.705
You know those TSA machines
show you naked?

18:41.790 --> 18:43.374
I <i>got</i> to look good
for that.

18:49.914 --> 18:54.868
♪ Whoa-oa, whoa ♪

18:54.919 --> 18:57.721
♪ whoa-oa, whoa ♪

19:00.892 --> 19:02.593
♪ Whoa-oa ♪

19:02.677 --> 19:03.927
Hello?

19:03.995 --> 19:05.963
Hi, Mr. Adams.
I'm calling from the clinic.

19:06.031 --> 19:09.767
We need you to come back in
and retest as soon as you can.

19:09.851 --> 19:11.852
Why?
Is there, uh, a problem?

19:11.903 --> 19:12.920
Yes.

19:13.021 --> 19:14.688
Actually,
it looks like the lab

19:14.739 --> 19:17.157
had a mix-up
with your urine sample.

19:17.225 --> 19:19.276
Okay. Are you sure?

19:19.360 --> 19:21.912
Well, unless you're pregnant,
we're pretty sure.

19:21.996 --> 19:26.834
♪ I was saving up
for the long winter ♪

19:26.901 --> 19:31.839
♪ summers we'd hide out
in my car ♪

19:31.906 --> 19:33.740
♪ when it broke down,
we didn't care ♪

19:33.792 --> 19:35.042
Hey.

19:35.093 --> 19:37.294
What's wrong?
You okay?

19:37.378 --> 19:39.630
♪ Mine is yours ♪

19:39.714 --> 19:41.548
We need to talk.

19:41.599 --> 19:43.851
♪ What is mine is yours ♪

19:47.021 --> 19:49.973
♪ What is mine is yours ♪

19:50.058 --> 19:52.259
Ball four.
Take your base.

19:52.310 --> 19:55.195
Yay, Madison!

19:55.263 --> 19:57.865
Let's go, Sharks!

19:57.932 --> 19:59.233
Dude,
what happened to Quinn?

19:59.284 --> 20:02.286
Uh, she had a few last-minute
things to take car of.

20:02.370 --> 20:04.271
I think she wanted
to get a spray tan.

20:04.322 --> 20:05.789
She'll be here.
Nice one, Madison!

20:07.742 --> 20:10.043
Way to go!

20:10.111 --> 20:12.379
I'd like
the panther, please.

20:12.447 --> 20:14.581
Actually, the panther
is our darkest shade.

20:14.632 --> 20:16.500
I really wouldn't
recommend that for you.

20:16.584 --> 20:18.669
Oh, that's okay.
I'll be fine.

20:18.753 --> 20:20.437
Just one panther, please.

20:20.505 --> 20:21.839
Okay.

20:23.758 --> 20:25.625
She'll be here.

20:25.677 --> 20:27.060
But you know
who won't be here?

20:28.596 --> 20:31.148
Ian.

20:31.232 --> 20:33.066
We got to talk to Ian.

20:33.134 --> 20:35.802
I know. I'll do it.

20:35.854 --> 20:37.437
It'd probably be better
if I talk to him.

20:37.489 --> 20:39.139
Why?

20:39.190 --> 20:41.225
'Cause you're bad cop
and I'm good cop.

20:41.292 --> 20:42.342
Why am I bad cop?

20:42.410 --> 20:44.194
Real-- it -- okay.

20:44.279 --> 20:45.979
Might be the, uh,
the bar fights,

20:46.030 --> 20:47.614
the shouting matches
in public,

20:47.665 --> 20:48.665
the murderous father.

20:48.750 --> 20:50.317
Weak.

20:50.368 --> 20:52.085
Maybe Julian
should talk to him.

20:52.153 --> 20:53.353
Why not me?

20:53.421 --> 20:54.838
Because you're not good cop.

20:54.923 --> 20:56.489
You're more like
officer friendly.

20:56.541 --> 20:57.991
Julian nearly lost Brooke.

20:58.042 --> 21:00.093
He should talk to him,
if he wants to.

21:06.017 --> 21:08.001
Where we going, anyway?

21:08.052 --> 21:10.304
Just taking
a little drive.

21:13.841 --> 21:17.361
<i>"They saw his face</i>
<i>grow stern and cold,</i>

21:17.445 --> 21:20.063
<i>they saw his muscles strain."</i>

21:22.700 --> 21:25.536
<i>"And they knew that Casey</i>

21:25.620 --> 21:28.539
<i>wouldn't let that ball</i>
<i>go by again."</i>

21:30.524 --> 21:32.910
Strike three.

21:32.977 --> 21:35.128
You're out.

21:44.160 --> 21:45.711
All right, this is it.

21:45.826 --> 21:47.243
We need one run to tie,
two to win.

21:47.310 --> 21:49.245
I say we win it right here.
No extra innings.

21:49.312 --> 21:52.314
No extra innings.
<i>Definitely</i> no extra innings.

21:55.318 --> 21:57.169
Now, you all know
I'm moving to New York

21:57.254 --> 21:59.005
and this is gonna be
my only game.

21:59.089 --> 22:00.539
I need a batter,
coach!

22:00.624 --> 22:02.508
So I just wanted to express --
All right, that's it.

22:02.592 --> 22:04.010
Top of the order.
Chuck, Madison, Jamie.

22:04.094 --> 22:06.045
Let's go.

22:08.899 --> 22:11.300
All right, Sharks,
we got this. Come on!

22:11.351 --> 22:14.487
Whoo!

22:14.554 --> 22:16.338
Come on, Chuck.
Look alive, buddy!

22:16.390 --> 22:19.859
♪ She put her head on my head
and with teary eyes she said ♪

22:19.943 --> 22:22.228
There he is,
Chuck Skolnick!

22:22.312 --> 22:26.065
♪ With a rose in her hand
and a candle... ♪

22:26.149 --> 22:27.533
These are for good luck.

22:29.119 --> 22:32.321
♪ She put her head
on my head... ♪

22:32.372 --> 22:33.956
Yeah, nice.
Nice.

22:34.023 --> 22:36.075
You got this, buddy.

22:36.159 --> 22:38.961
Let's go, Skolnick!
Free root beer for a hit!

22:39.028 --> 22:40.713
Yeah!

22:40.797 --> 22:42.148
Whoo! Come on, Chuck!

22:42.215 --> 22:43.198
Let's go, Skolnick!

22:43.250 --> 22:44.700
Whoo!
Come on, Chuck!

22:44.751 --> 22:46.869
Let's go, Skolnick!

22:46.920 --> 22:51.057
♪ Makes me stronger ♪

22:51.141 --> 22:54.510
♪ makes me wiser ♪

22:54.561 --> 22:56.345
♪ makes me stronger ♪

22:56.396 --> 22:57.513
♪ makes me stronger ♪

22:59.316 --> 23:01.067
Whoo!

23:01.151 --> 23:04.353
♪ Makes me stronger, stronger ♪

23:07.491 --> 23:09.692
Yes!
Nice, Chuck!

23:09.743 --> 23:12.394
All right! Ha ha!
We're having fun now!

23:12.446 --> 23:15.581
But we're having it fast.
Madison, you're up.

23:15.665 --> 23:18.117
Come on, Madison.
Boop, boop.

23:18.201 --> 23:20.786
Fast fun, fast fun.

23:20.871 --> 23:22.755
Let's go, Sharks!
Hi, handsome.

23:24.791 --> 23:26.909
Ohh!
I'm so tan, right?

23:26.960 --> 23:28.294
Do you love it?

23:28.361 --> 23:30.129
Mm-hmm.

23:30.213 --> 23:32.765
Don't forget about our date later.
Mnh-mnh.

23:34.134 --> 23:37.686
Madison. Madison,
take your time, okay?

23:37.754 --> 23:39.054
You wait for your right pitch,

23:39.106 --> 23:40.523
and you tie this thing up
for us.

23:40.590 --> 23:42.858
I'm talking extra innings.

23:42.926 --> 23:44.810
Free baseball, Sharks!

23:44.895 --> 23:48.314
We like that.

23:48.398 --> 23:54.954
♪ With a stone in my heart,
I stood up, and I got strong ♪

24:18.845 --> 24:20.513
So, how's your dad
doing, Ian?

24:20.597 --> 24:23.131
I mean,
now that he's resigned.

24:23.183 --> 24:25.851
I don't know.
However, I guess.

24:25.936 --> 24:28.287
He mostly spends time
on that stupid boat.

24:28.355 --> 24:30.022
You know what's good
about boats?

24:31.324 --> 24:33.976
They float.

24:34.027 --> 24:35.277
Cars, not so much.

24:37.614 --> 24:39.081
Where are we going,
again?

24:39.148 --> 24:41.200
Right here.

24:41.284 --> 24:42.751
We're going right here.

25:21.958 --> 25:25.544
I'll never
forget this place.

25:25.629 --> 25:27.997
♪ You know how it goes ♪

25:28.048 --> 25:31.217
I was standing right about here
when I saw Brooke.

25:31.301 --> 25:33.502
And she looked
so relieved,

25:33.553 --> 25:35.638
like maybe...
For a moment,

25:35.705 --> 25:37.840
everything
was gonna be okay.

25:37.891 --> 25:40.542
I was proud of her,
you know?

25:40.594 --> 25:43.012
For staying
to help Jamie.

25:43.063 --> 25:44.563
I mean,
he's just a kid.

25:44.648 --> 25:46.899
Just a scared kid
who wanted to believe

25:46.983 --> 25:48.851
that everything
would be okay,

25:48.902 --> 25:51.904
and that adults
would <i>make</i> it okay

25:51.988 --> 25:54.323
and be heroic and strong

25:54.390 --> 25:58.193
and everything they're supposed
to be for a boy like that.

25:58.245 --> 25:59.862
♪ Hard to be ♪

25:59.913 --> 26:02.615
And then the Wagoneer
came from right there.

26:05.585 --> 26:08.954
♪ Hard to be ♪

26:09.039 --> 26:10.873
They're lucky to be alive!

26:12.542 --> 26:14.126
Yeah, man, I'm so sorry.

26:14.210 --> 26:15.861
You know,
my dad, he --

26:15.929 --> 26:18.013
He hasn't had a drink
since your mom died.

26:18.081 --> 26:20.432
♪ ...To believe that...♪

26:20.517 --> 26:21.967
That's not true.

26:22.052 --> 26:25.087
He was also coming from Raleigh
that night.

26:25.138 --> 26:26.588
And he wouldn't
have been coming

26:26.640 --> 26:28.440
from that direction.

26:28.525 --> 26:30.759
So maybe he got turned around
in the storm. I don't know.

26:30.810 --> 26:32.528
Maybe it was <i>you,</i> Ian.

26:32.595 --> 26:35.781
♪ ...Fight it,
we should all be satisfied... ♪

26:35.865 --> 26:37.700
It was, wasn't it?

26:37.767 --> 26:40.986
♪ ...With this
magical explanation ♪

26:41.071 --> 26:42.604
Come on, guys.
He told you he did it.

26:42.656 --> 26:43.656
He resigned.

26:43.740 --> 26:44.907
And you let him!

26:44.958 --> 26:46.775
You got drunk,

26:46.826 --> 26:48.443
nearly killed my wife
and Nathan's son,

26:48.495 --> 26:49.912
and then just drove away

26:49.963 --> 26:51.747
and let your father
take the blame!

26:53.133 --> 26:55.250
Look at me!

26:55.302 --> 26:57.586
You probably didn't even
say "thank you."

26:57.637 --> 27:00.222
♪ Hard to be ♪

27:00.289 --> 27:02.474
You know what?
You guys are my agents.

27:02.559 --> 27:05.177
You're should be <i>thrilled</i>
<i>that we dodged a bullet,</i>

27:05.261 --> 27:07.930
that everyone's okay,
everything's been dealt with.

27:07.981 --> 27:09.181
Thrilled...

27:09.265 --> 27:11.483
That you drove drunk,
left our families to die,

27:11.601 --> 27:13.068
and your family
to pay for it?

27:13.136 --> 27:14.603
What the hell
is wrong with you?

27:16.690 --> 27:19.191
Guys, I got scouts
coming to see me.

27:19.275 --> 27:21.610
I am this close
to being someone.

27:21.661 --> 27:24.029
I couldn't stay here.
I couldn't.

27:24.114 --> 27:25.664
I didn't have a choice.

27:25.749 --> 27:27.666
Oh, you had a choice.

27:27.784 --> 27:30.252
Whatever.
This is ridiculous.

27:32.922 --> 27:33.706
Clay!
Clay!

27:37.994 --> 27:39.795
Are you
out of your mind?!

27:39.846 --> 27:42.381
You had no choice?!
You chose to be a coward!

27:47.387 --> 27:49.504
You know what?
You guys are fired!

27:49.556 --> 27:51.724
I might even
sue you for this!

27:57.864 --> 27:59.114
Get off me!

28:03.352 --> 28:05.154
Come here!

28:05.205 --> 28:06.238
Get off!

28:06.322 --> 28:07.990
You like that?!

28:08.041 --> 28:10.209
How does that feel?!
Stop!

28:10.293 --> 28:11.960
Stop!

28:12.028 --> 28:14.463
Don't you wish there was
somebody here to help you now?!

28:16.032 --> 28:17.633
Go on!

28:17.700 --> 28:20.502
Go throw your ball and be whoever
it is you think you're gonna be!

28:39.406 --> 28:40.906
My son
said to give that to you.

28:46.329 --> 28:47.663
I couldn't stay!

28:47.730 --> 28:49.698
I just couldn't!

28:52.118 --> 28:54.036
Well, now maybe you can stay
and think about it.

28:54.087 --> 28:55.754
Enjoy the walk.

29:07.469 --> 29:09.637
All right, Madison, come on!
No outs!

29:09.704 --> 29:12.423
We only need one, Madison!
Don't mess it up!

29:12.507 --> 29:18.846
♪ I open the door, and there you
are standing right before me ♪

29:18.897 --> 29:21.715
♪ you open my hand ♪

29:21.766 --> 29:25.069
Yeah!
Go, go, go, go, Madison!

29:27.689 --> 29:31.442
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

29:31.526 --> 29:34.278
♪ you are my perfect kind of ♪

29:34.362 --> 29:36.430
You're safe here.
Stop, stop.

29:36.498 --> 29:37.948
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

29:38.033 --> 29:40.584
All right!

29:40.669 --> 29:42.203
Come on, Jamie,
you can do this!

29:42.270 --> 29:43.087
Quinn?

29:44.673 --> 29:46.590
Is that a spray tan?

29:46.675 --> 29:48.425
Yeah.
It's the panther.

29:53.215 --> 29:56.517
♪ Can you take me out
to see... ♪

29:56.584 --> 29:59.520
Nice and slow.
Take your time.

29:59.587 --> 30:02.106
Hey.

30:02.190 --> 30:05.259
Let date night begin.

30:07.479 --> 30:09.980
Here I come.

30:10.065 --> 30:13.534
♪ Though it's just
the beginning ♪

30:13.601 --> 30:15.435
♪ that this is gonna last ♪

30:15.487 --> 30:17.604
Babe?

30:17.656 --> 30:19.273
Now, then...

30:21.076 --> 30:23.294
Oh, no!

30:23.378 --> 30:25.746
I think if we dunked you,
we could make tea.
Oh, my God!

30:25.797 --> 30:26.747
No!

30:26.798 --> 30:28.832
No, no, no!

30:28.917 --> 30:30.584
Well, maybe
some of it'll stick to me.

30:30.635 --> 30:31.802
I could use the color.

30:33.421 --> 30:35.055
♪ Oh, oh ♪

30:38.260 --> 30:40.394
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

30:40.461 --> 30:42.763
Can I interest you in a hot shower?
Yes.

30:42.814 --> 30:46.317
♪ You are my perfect kind of ♪

30:46.401 --> 30:49.636
All right.
Come on, Jamie, you got this.

30:49.688 --> 30:52.472
Let's get a hit.

30:57.312 --> 30:58.362
Thanks.

31:02.150 --> 31:03.334
So...

31:05.587 --> 31:07.755
...I owe you an apology.

31:07.822 --> 31:09.590
I was so sure
you were like my dad,

31:09.657 --> 31:12.042
I couldn't see you
any other way.

31:12.127 --> 31:14.295
Well...

31:14.362 --> 31:16.764
Then that makes us even.

31:16.831 --> 31:19.133
I was so sure
you were like my son

31:19.184 --> 31:21.352
that I couldn't see you
as the "A" student

31:21.436 --> 31:22.636
you turned out to be.

31:22.687 --> 31:24.171
"A" student?

31:24.222 --> 31:25.222
Really?

31:25.290 --> 31:26.473
"A" minus.

31:27.976 --> 31:30.444
I understand you're no longer
representing my son.

31:30.511 --> 31:32.946
That's right.

31:33.014 --> 31:35.065
Admit it --
when I asked you not to,

31:35.150 --> 31:36.667
you thought it was because

31:36.735 --> 31:39.186
I felt you weren't
good enough for him.

31:39.237 --> 31:42.356
But maybe I thought <i>he</i> wasn't
good enough for <i>you</i>

31:42.407 --> 31:45.492
and that agency you have
with your partner, the Muppet.

31:45.543 --> 31:47.828
Clay Evans.

31:47.879 --> 31:49.196
Fortitude.

31:49.247 --> 31:52.750
Integrity
as a mission statement.

31:52.834 --> 31:55.169
Not bad.

32:00.558 --> 32:03.811
I promised my wife, Catherine,
I'd do this someday --

32:03.878 --> 32:06.146
sail off to nowhere.

32:06.214 --> 32:09.817
No lectures,
no papers, no clocks.

32:09.884 --> 32:13.654
Actually, I promised her
we'd do it together.

32:15.690 --> 32:17.724
Time gets away
from you.

32:25.200 --> 32:27.734
You know, I don't speak
with my father.

32:29.754 --> 32:31.922
Sometimes I feel guilty
about that,

32:32.006 --> 32:34.925
but I know in my heart
that's the way it has to be.

32:35.009 --> 32:36.677
So, one of these nights,

32:36.744 --> 32:40.547
when you find your corner of
heaven or your sliver of peace

32:40.598 --> 32:42.383
and you're feeling guilty

32:42.434 --> 32:46.136
about the distance
between you and your son...

32:46.221 --> 32:47.587
I don't know.

32:47.639 --> 32:50.641
Maybe it just...helps to know
that you're not the only one

32:50.725 --> 32:53.444
going through
something like that.

32:58.099 --> 32:59.783
Well, there's no time
like now

32:59.868 --> 33:01.435
to start
the rest of your life.

33:04.038 --> 33:06.440
Thanks for the beer,
profes--

33:06.491 --> 33:07.941
um, Mr. Kellerman.

33:07.992 --> 33:09.543
Call me August.

33:09.610 --> 33:11.545
Where's Dogust,
by the way?

33:11.612 --> 33:12.880
He's here. Dogust!

33:12.947 --> 33:14.081
Hey!

33:14.132 --> 33:17.084
Look who's here
to see you!

33:17.135 --> 33:18.285
Yes. Look at this.

33:18.336 --> 33:20.337
Every Captain
needs a first mate.

33:20.422 --> 33:22.389
There he is.
Hey, pal.

33:22.457 --> 33:25.008
Good to see you again.

33:25.093 --> 33:27.794
All right.

33:27.846 --> 33:29.263
Take care.

33:29.314 --> 33:31.732
All the best.

33:31.799 --> 33:33.800
Come on.
Let's go sailing.

33:33.852 --> 33:35.635
Come on, Dogust.

33:35.687 --> 33:37.521
Come on, my boy.

33:43.278 --> 33:46.146
Mr. Scott.

33:46.197 --> 33:48.165
They still developing
those condos

33:48.249 --> 33:50.167
at that basketball court
of yours?

33:50.251 --> 33:51.835
The Rivercourt.
Yeah.

33:51.920 --> 33:54.004
Two words --

33:54.088 --> 33:56.290
Snipey Plover.

33:58.209 --> 33:59.960
It's a bird.

34:03.348 --> 34:07.434
Okay, Catherine,
here we go.

34:07.502 --> 34:10.020
You too, Dogust. You too.

34:14.976 --> 34:17.010
Yeah.

34:55.433 --> 34:57.050
Strike one.

34:58.875 --> 35:00.709
Time!

35:00.793 --> 35:02.294
Time!

35:04.130 --> 35:05.914
How you doing?

35:05.999 --> 35:08.083
Okay, I guess.
Yeah?

35:08.167 --> 35:09.251
Feeling nervous?

35:09.335 --> 35:10.669
Yeah,
I always felt nervous

35:10.720 --> 35:12.754
at the free-throw line.

35:12.839 --> 35:15.674
But listen, there's something
I forgot to tell you about today

35:15.725 --> 35:17.259
that I should have.

35:17.343 --> 35:19.644
It's just a game, okay?

35:19.712 --> 35:21.596
Grandpa Dan always
used to make me feel

35:21.681 --> 35:24.399
like it was life or death,
but it's not.

35:24.484 --> 35:26.435
Now, you got a couple
good strikes coming,

35:26.519 --> 35:28.020
so just give it
your best shot.

35:28.071 --> 35:30.405
You're a good hitter.
You can do this.

35:30.490 --> 35:32.557
No matter what,
we're both getting ice cream,

35:32.608 --> 35:33.859
so either way
we're good.

35:33.910 --> 35:35.560
All right?

35:35.611 --> 35:37.329
Okay, coach, let's go.
All right.

35:37.396 --> 35:39.230
Go get 'em, Jamie Scott.

35:39.282 --> 35:40.449
Okay.

36:16.319 --> 36:19.071
I couldn't do it.

36:19.122 --> 36:21.656
I drove to see Dan,
but I couldn't go in.

36:23.159 --> 36:25.077
Maybe one day.

36:25.128 --> 36:30.582
♪ What if the storm ends
and I don't see you? ♪

36:30.633 --> 36:33.001
<i>"The sneer is gone</i>
<i>from Casey's lip,</i>

36:33.086 --> 36:35.971
<i>his teeth are clenched</i>
<i>in hate."</i>

36:36.055 --> 36:37.806
♪ Ever again ♪

36:37.890 --> 36:40.291
♪ the perfect halo... ♪

36:40.343 --> 36:42.694
<i>"He pounds</i>
<i>with cruel violence...</i>

36:42.762 --> 36:46.631
<i>"His bat upon the plate.</i>

36:46.682 --> 36:48.934
<i>"He signaled to the pitcher,</i>

36:48.985 --> 36:51.436
<i>and once more</i>
<i>the spheroid flew."</i>

36:53.022 --> 36:54.573
♪ ...The silver-forked sky ♪

36:54.640 --> 36:58.026
<i>"But Casey still ignored it,</i>
<i>and the umpire said..."</i>

36:58.111 --> 36:59.778
Strike two!

36:59.829 --> 37:01.079
♪ ...I will follow ♪

37:01.147 --> 37:02.831
Come on, Jamie, come on.

37:02.915 --> 37:05.316
Come on, Jamie!
You can do it!

37:05.368 --> 37:06.651
I know you can.

37:06.702 --> 37:09.037
♪ ...Found you ♪

37:09.122 --> 37:12.290
♪ I don't wanna run ♪

37:12.341 --> 37:14.509
♪ just overwhelm me ♪

37:18.664 --> 37:21.099
All my life,
I've wanted to fly.

37:21.167 --> 37:23.718
And lately,
I've been feeling...

37:23.803 --> 37:25.554
A sense of obligation.

37:25.638 --> 37:27.839
That's why you've been
spending time with Chuck, right?

37:27.890 --> 37:29.524
That's right.

37:29.609 --> 37:32.611
But...It's more
than that.

37:32.678 --> 37:36.565
I needed to take that drug test
to join the Air Force.

37:36.649 --> 37:38.016
What?

37:38.067 --> 37:41.203
Oh, my gosh.
And did you join the Air Force?

37:41.287 --> 37:42.520
Not yet.

37:42.572 --> 37:45.874
There's still a chance I could,
but...

37:45.958 --> 37:47.759
♪ ...As you are now... ♪

37:47.827 --> 37:50.045
I'd rather stay here
with you because...

37:50.129 --> 37:52.047
♪ ...Ever again? ♪

37:52.131 --> 37:53.915
♪ the perfect halo... ♪

37:54.000 --> 37:56.534
...You're pregnant,
Alex.

37:56.636 --> 37:58.153
We're pregnant.

37:58.221 --> 38:01.089
♪ Sets you off against
the planet's last dance ♪

38:01.174 --> 38:03.725
Hey, it's okay.

38:03.809 --> 38:05.177
It's gonna be okay.

38:05.228 --> 38:08.013
I'm gonna be right here.

38:08.064 --> 38:09.648
No, no, no, no,
it's not...

38:14.053 --> 38:16.354
But you would stay with me?

38:16.405 --> 38:18.406
Of course.

38:18.491 --> 38:22.727
♪ ...Like I have found you ♪

38:22.778 --> 38:25.163
What do you mean
it's -- it's not okay?

38:25.231 --> 38:29.701
Now <i>I</i> have something
to tell <i>you.</i>

38:38.928 --> 38:40.912
Hey, handsome.

38:40.963 --> 38:42.931
Hi.

38:45.518 --> 38:47.602
I turned down the job.
In New York? Why?

38:55.061 --> 38:58.313
When I was living there
and running Clothes Over Bros,

38:58.397 --> 39:01.650
my office looked out
on this building nearby,

39:01.734 --> 39:03.618
and on the rooftop
was a playground

39:03.703 --> 39:06.288
where all the grade-school kids
would have recess.

39:06.372 --> 39:10.108
And some days
when things were crazy --

39:10.159 --> 39:12.327
which was most days --

39:12.411 --> 39:14.746
I'd look out, and I'd watch
those kids run around,

39:14.797 --> 39:18.550
and I'd think,
"that's no way to play."

39:18.617 --> 39:19.884
I mean, I love New York,

39:19.952 --> 39:22.504
but living in constant fear

39:22.588 --> 39:25.373
of losing the kickball over
the roof of your playground

39:25.441 --> 39:28.026
is kind of a rough way
to grow up.

39:28.094 --> 39:29.394
So you turned down
the job

39:29.461 --> 39:31.396
because the schools
have playgrounds on the roof?

39:31.463 --> 39:33.815
I turned down the job
because I don't want our child

39:33.899 --> 39:36.268
to have a playground
on the roof.

39:36.352 --> 39:40.905
Unless it's the roof of my store
here in Tree Hill.

39:40.973 --> 39:43.575
Tree Hill...
Okay, you're losing me.

39:43.642 --> 39:45.577
Chase had to take
a drug test,

39:45.644 --> 39:49.030
but a guy in Kid Cudi's posse
made him take a hit of a joint,

39:49.115 --> 39:52.917
so he asked Alex to pee in a cup
for him because she's sober.

39:52.985 --> 39:54.336
Except Alex
isn't really sober

39:54.420 --> 39:57.172
because she accidentally ate
some of Quinn's pot brownies,

39:57.256 --> 39:58.757
so Alex came over
to ask you,

39:58.824 --> 40:00.792
because her and Chase
are getting closer,

40:00.843 --> 40:02.961
and she wanted to be the one
to help him,

40:03.012 --> 40:04.879
but you weren't home,
so Alex asked me.

40:04.964 --> 40:10.501
And the lab called Chase
and said that he's pregnant.

40:10.553 --> 40:12.503
What?

40:12.555 --> 40:15.357
So Chase told Alex,

40:15.441 --> 40:18.276
and Alex told me,

40:18.344 --> 40:20.729
and I took
a pregnancy test.

40:22.898 --> 40:25.033
We're pregnant.

40:25.117 --> 40:26.985
Baby!

40:30.039 --> 40:33.191
I knew you could do it.

40:33.242 --> 40:38.496
♪ What if the storm ends
and I don't see you ♪

40:38.547 --> 40:44.202
♪ as you are now ever again? ♪

40:44.253 --> 40:46.137
♪ the perfect halo ♪

40:46.205 --> 40:47.972
<i>"Oh, somewhere</i>
<i>in this favored land</i>

40:48.040 --> 40:50.058
<i>the sun is shining bright."</i>

40:50.142 --> 40:53.094
♪ Sets you off against... ♪

40:53.179 --> 40:55.713
<i>"The band is playing somewhere,</i>

40:55.765 --> 40:57.482
<i>and somewhere</i>
<i>hearts are light."</i>

40:57.549 --> 40:59.234
All right, come on, Jamie!
You can do it, son!

40:59.318 --> 41:02.937
<i>"And somewhere</i>
<i>men are laughing,</i>

41:03.022 --> 41:06.074
<i>and somewhere children shout."</i>

41:06.158 --> 41:08.993
♪ ...That I will follow ♪

41:09.061 --> 41:11.396
<i>That somewhere is right here.</i>

41:11.447 --> 41:15.450
♪ Like I have found you ♪

41:15.518 --> 41:19.537
<i>Because Casey</i>
<i>might have struck out,</i>

41:19.605 --> 41:22.707
<i>but Casey's last name</i>
<i>wasn't "Scott."</i>

